@NODE "Introduction" "How did it come to this?"
@NEXT "Instal"
@PREV "MAIN"
@TOC "MAIN"
Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
It all began when Shai Hulud, the sysop of Neon-Noon BBS, connected some
dudes on the networks he was connected on and decided to make more and
frequent use of it. This involved transferring the TIC files received from
bulletin boards like Xenolink. Well, a year back I programmed TicMover but
that bugged giganticly, so, I recoded it from scratch and bumped into
problems like DayDream not having a script bulker (uploder) like RoboWriter
(message writer that adds messages from shell or script), so, I decided to
code this BULK utility to.

It has grown from a simple add on util to a fully DayDream support util,
it checks the data files, it uses the listings in a save way, longnames are
detected and more... see the features chapter.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Instal" "Installation"
@NEXT "Usage"
@PREV "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"
Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Simple, copy Dream BULK anywhere you want, it might be a good idea to copy
it to DayDream:Utils/ or something. It does not need a configuration file,
except for the DATA files of DayDream itself.
It reads DIRECTLY from the DAT files and extracts every data it
needs. Unlike TICMover a lot months back, it does not need megabytes of
config file to be able to upload ANYTHING, it just needs the standard data
files for DayDream, as I said.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "How to use..."
@NEXT "Required"
@PREV "Instal"
@TOC "MAIN"
Usage
~~~~~
First of all:
Be sure that the server is started up, else the program does not start, it
needs the server to make a save directory list entry, or a save uploadlog
data file entry.

Syntax: DreamBulk FILE/A,UPLOADER/A,CONFERENCE/N,FILEAREA/N,DESCRIPTION/A,REPLACE/S

This is all fairly simple, the only thing needing attention is DESCRIPTION.
This MUST be a FILE! And NOT a single line of description or something
like that. That way it is compatible with FILE_ID.DIZ files etc etc

Make ssure that UPLOADER is the name of someone located in the Userbase,
if the name can not be found, slotnumber 0 is used, that users records
are used, he is given the credits if needed and his slotnumber is put
in the UploadLog.DAT.

People who are using LONGNAMES in one or more conferences are gonna ask
the question: but does it support longnames?
Well I have been working my ass off so that DreamBULK uses the DATa files
of DayDream as much as possible. This made it possible to upload with no
extra configuration files. So therefore, Longnames are automatically detected
in the concerning conference, also through the DATa files, the Uploader gets
his credits if configured in the data files. This and much more is all
extracted, added or read from the DATa files.

NOTE:
REPLACE is a boolean, to turn it on, just put REPLACE somewhere behind the
dreambulk command, this replace feature defaults to OFF (when you do not specify
it behind DreamBulk). What it does is, it replace a file with the same name if
this file already existed in the destination path/conference/filearea...

    Example:

        DreamBulk ram:ddbbs129.lha sysop 15 4 ram:file_id.diz

        ^^^^^^^
        this one would NOT replace the file ddbbs129.lha if it already existed
        and will tell you that the file already existed and then exits.

        DreamBulk ram:ddbbs129.lha sysop 15 4 ram:file_id.diz REPLACE

        ^^^^^^^
        this one WOULD replace the file because REPLACE has been added...
        try it yourself...

    this feature can be handy to update files on your BBS... soon I will enable
    this feature to alter the file id in the file catalog aswell...

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Required" "What you need..."
@NEXT "Credits"
@PREV "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"
Required
~~~~~~~~
Required are the following:

-   Amiga Based System :)

-   OS 2.04 or higher

-   DayDream Bulletin Board System

-   DATA Files of DayDream BBS (config file of DD MUST be compiled)

-   100kb of memory for copy buffer, config data, etc etc
@ENDNODE

