@NODE "Restrictions" "Restrictions"
@NEXT "Features"
@PREV "Credits"
@TOC "MAIN"
Restrictions
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Some restrictions, some were intended for the easy of use (that you as user
don't have to enter kilometers of arguments) and some intended to make
coding life easier for me :).

Don't get me wrong, they are NOT bugs, just restrictions:

    -   The upload BPS rate (UploadLog.DAT) is set to 57600
        maybe in the future this will be configurable but, for now,
        I don't think it is needed, and it beats the 0 BPS entry that
        DayDream enters in the uploadlog for local uploads.

    -   I assumed that the setting NO WILD FLAG FILE ALLOWED was intended
        for not allowing #?, #, ? and * characters in the filename. This could
        be wrong, but since the doc is unclear about this (DayDream docs) I am
        not sure.

    -   File that is uploaded is NOT! checked for virus/checksum etc. this would
        complicate things extremely since most of DayDream sysops use DayDream
        Door checkers. If you DO want some kind of check method (integrity
        or something) mail me and give me suggestions (mail adress below).

    -   Dupechecking is also not done by external progs, the same reasons apply
        here as for the filechecking. Suggestions to address below.
        The only dupechecking is done by the bulker itself and is only done for
        the current directory the bulker is uploading to. This means that it checks
        if the file already exists in the path the file is going to be copied to.
        If it already exists, DreamBULK exits except when you specified it should
        replace the file with the same name.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Features" "What do I get?"
@NEXT "ToDo"
@PREV "Restrictions"
@TOC "MAIN"
Features
~~~~~~~~
- Upload files from cli/script/etc

- Handles 18-chars longname directories

- Handles 12-chars directories

- Uses data of DayDream (conferences.dat etc)

- NO extra configuration file needed

- UploadLog.DAT entry with all data specified in developer structures of DD

- If credits should be given, the user specified as Uploader is given these
  credits, user records are adjusted.

- Slotnumber of Uploader is also used for making an entry in the UploadLog.DAT

- Upload signature is taken from user records

- Free download tag is taken frorm DayDream.DAT

- FULL FreeDownloads.DAT support

- FULL WildCard support (in FreeDownloads.DAT and only #? fully supported)

- INTERNAL Copy program, copies a lot faster

- Size of copy buffer is taken from DayDream.DAT

- DayDream server now handles filelisting addings! This will ensure you
  that no problems will occur when a user has been logged on while you
  are bulking some files. (shared file errors don't occur because the server
  handles this)

- Extremely fast because data is read from memory and not from disc

- Replacing of files is possible if requested

@ENDNODE

